list.comment: Main: This class contains the main method that runs the program. It reads the orders and store data from JSON files using the JsonConverter class and assigns each order to a picker based on their available time. It also sorts the orders by the completeBy time in ascending order and prints the picking schedule for each picker. JsonConverter: This class contains two static methods that convert JSON files to Order and Store objects. It uses the Gson library to parse JSON data. Order: This class represents an order object. It has properties such as orderId, orderValue, pickingTime, and completeBy, which are read from the JSON file. Store: This class represents a store object. It has properties such as name, address, pickingStartTime, and pickers, which are read from the JSON file. The pickers property is a list of picker names who are available for picking orders.
